  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7099 sitting just above the GEX flip at 6995 and below the massive +5152.5M gamma wall at 7100, dealers are currently long gamma and likely buying this dip given the -7.7% recent decline. The PIN regime with heavy positive gamma concentration at 7100-7200 suggests dealers will continue providing liquidity by buying weakness and selling strength, creating a stabilizing force around current levels. Key watch points are the 7100 gamma wall above (dealers sell rallies into this zone) and the 6995 flip level below (break risks accelerated selling as dealers flip to short gamma).\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect choppy trading with a magnetic pull back toward 7100-7150.",
